ma.","Italian (southern):","occupational name from medieval Greek <i>kontostablēs</i> ‘chamberlain’, from medieval Latin <i>comes stabuli</i>, literally ‘count of the stable’ (see   Constable  )."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Eadnoth the Constable was born about 1035, in Bristol, England, United Kingdom. He married Rissa de Dursley in 1048, in Gloucestershire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. He died in 1068, in Bleadon, Somerset, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 34."},"et":{"about 1035–1068":"umbes 1035–1068","1035–1069":"1035–1069","1060–1125":"1060–1125","1067–1142":"1067–1142","1035–1068":"1035–1068","1048":"1048","1125":"1125","1069":"1069","1068":"1068","1035":"1035","1067":"1067","about 1035":"umbes 1035","1142":"1142","1060":"1060","about 1067":"umbes 1067","Bristol, Gloucestershire, England":"Bristol, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Gloucestershire, Anglo-Saxon England":"Gloucestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Berkeley, Gloucestershire, England":"Berkeley, Gloucestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Bristol, Gloucestershire, Anglo-Saxon England":"Bristol, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Bleadon, Somerset, England":"Bleadon, Somerset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1035–1068":"noin 1035–1068","1035–1069":"1035–1069","1060–1125":"1060–1125","1067–1142":"1067–1142","1035–1068":"1035–1068","1048":"1048","1125":"1125","1069":"1069","1068":"1068","1035":"1035","1067":"1067","about 1035":"noin 1035","1142":"1142","1060":"1060","about 1067":"noin 1067","Bristol, Gloucestershire, England":"Bristol, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Gloucestershire, Anglo-Saxon England":"Gloucestershire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Berkeley, Gloucestershire, England":"Berkeley, Gloucestershire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Bristol, Gloucestershire, Anglo-Saxon England":"Bristol, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Bleadon, Somerset, England":"Bleadon, Somerset, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"about 1035–1068":"en